314	 *  forward pass over `text`. At each `<<PREFIX:` encountered (first
315	 *  match against any registered prefix wins — they don't overlap because
316	 *  all prefixes are `<<UPPERCASE:`), we find the matching top-level
317	 *  `>>` and hand the inner substring to that prefix's handler.
318	 *
319	 *  This outer-first strategy is what prevents a nested `<<GOAL_DONE:>>`
320	 *  inside a `<<RESTART:...>>` reason from being extracted as a real
321	 *  GOAL_DONE: the scanner sees the `<<RESTART:` opener first, walks to
322	 *  its balanced closer (tracking depth so inner `<<>>` pairs don't
323	 *  prematurely close), and consumes the whole span atomically.
324	 *
325	 *  Handler semantics (same as `replaceBalancedTokens`):
326	 *    • returns string → replaces the full `<<PREFIX:...>>` span
327	 *    • returns null  → token left verbatim, scanner continues past it
